name: DeRimbun Eco Cafe & Cooking Class
address: G29H+VH8, North Bajera, Selemadeg, Tabanan Regency, Bali 82162, Indonesia
review 1:
This cafe is located in Kusfarm, far from the city, so if you really need a secluded place to relax, I think this is a good place.

The food is tasty,  even though I think it needs more kicks in it. For example more variant in the greens/ side salad. For me, personally, mixing only lettuce and cucumber in the salad  is not appetizing. üòÑ

The staff are friendly and informative, even for a local guest.
I noticed the cafe staff found a bit of a difficulties in explaining the menu.
Since most of the guests are foreigners, I think more english training is necessary for them.
review 2:
Lovely cafe where you can sit and relax. Enjoy the soft music, koi‚Äôs and water falling.

Had a stay at the Kusfarm Bali so explored a lot of their menu. I can recommend their Tempeh Broccoli Bowl, Big portion and very tasty.

Only thing to mention is please make this restaurant Smoke Free, everytime the disgusting smell of sigarettes while eating.

The chicken teryaki was nice as well, order it with a starter because its salad and chicken and may not be enough.

Beef Rendang is very spicey, but also of high quality. Smaller portion as well.

Overall the portions are bit smaller, but the more space you have for a dessert

Breakfast is very nice as well, go discover that one yourself if you stay at the farm.

Prices are good with a variation from 30k to 120k.
